item.description:
Permissions policy In addition to the default authorization policy, Vanadium offers another built-in authorization policy based on the commonly used idea of a permissions map. Such an authorizer allows a wide range of policies controllable via editing lists that are given to a server as flags - no need to modify code.
{{# helpers.info }}
Vanadium also supports the use of a completely custom policy - the procedure for building one is covered in the custom authorizer tutorial.
